Wilmer McINTOSH, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 22274. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. Oct. 15, 1965. Donald C. Lehman, Thomas M. Bau-mer, Asst. U. S. Attys., Jacksonville, Fla., William A. Meadows, Jr., U. S. Atty., Southern District of Florida, William J. Hamilton, Jr., Sp. Asst, to U. S. Atty., Thomas M. Baumer, Asst. U. S. Atty., Middle District of Florida, for appellee.

Before JONES and BELL, Circuit Judges, and JOHNSON, District Judge.

PER CURIAM:

No error appearing, the judgment of the district court is

Affirmed.
